Text: Hunting before the actual hunt is so much fun!
Lady Delta, please don't go too far!
Ahahah! I know, I know!

The neglected areas around the villa have become a
haven for monsters native to the area.

Usually, it would be a pain to deal with, but for
once, I'm thankfulâ€”it gives Delta something to do.

It seems pretty dusty in here. Hasn't seen much use,
has it?

No. This villa primarily served as a safe house to
monitor the research activities in Laugus.

We have multiple locations like this throughout the
 Velgalta Empire.

So, as aristocrats within the Cult, your lives were
targeted?

Even without being a member of the Cult, being an
aristocrat alone paints a target on your back...
although some might not even realize it.

And being a member of the Cult of Diablos only
intensifies your suspicion of those around you,
doesn't it?

Well, if neither other aristocrats nor the Cult of
Diablos knows this place, it works in the Garden's
favor.

As for ownership of this villa...even if documents
are forged, we should express gratitude to the
paranoid Baron Herzog of that time.

...Not that this will improve the Garden's assessment
of you.
I understand.
Do you, really?
...What matters is my actions from here on out.

Exactly. So start by cleaning this place to make it
at least habitable!
Cleaning...?!

Really? As a former Baroness, you've never done any
cleaning before?
N-No, it's not like that!

This will serve as one of the Shadow Garden's new
bases.

It's not just a hideout to lie low and weather the
storm. It'll be a cozy sanctuary where you can
rest easy and sleep soundly...

So, with that in mind, make sure to clean it
thoroughly! Do it with your own hands, for
yourself!
U-Understood!

...That's right. Create a safe haven with your own
hands, No. 111.

Well then, guess I'll go and investigate the enemy's
activities!

...Aren't we leaving yet? Wasn't the main carriage
already loaded onto the ship from the start?

There's been a delay to the goods meant to be loaded.
Just keep quiet and wait.
*sigh* What're we transporting anyway?

No need for a mere mercenary like you to know. If you
want your pay, quit prying.
*sigh* What a pain...
Lady Epsilon...!
My guess was right.

(Combining the intel from Zeta, who is already here
in Velgalta, with the intel Iota gathered from the
trade city...)

(I deduced the Cult's scheme to transport the
possessed from Velgalta and the Templars'
covert operation upon having caught wind
of this.)

(The fragrance Delta detected was from the Templars,
who were already in place to counteract this plan...)

(By attacking the unit responsible for transporting
the extra cargo, they're delaying the departure of
the Cult's ship as we speak...)

(While the Cult isn't on as high alert as they were
with No. 93, they've still enlisted mercenary escorts
and seem prepared for the Templars.)

(...Well, not that they're that different than their
usual convoy.)
Well done, Lady Epsilon.

I barely had to weigh in with any tactical advice for
this operation.

Heheh... That's because I have a top-notch strategic
advisor.

Once you effectively laid out the available intel,
the path forward was pretty much obvious.
You honor me...!
...No. 111. I'll give you a rundown of the plan.

Your job is to protect the possessed who may be
imprisoned aboard the ship before the Templars
intervene.

Because...the Templars won't hesitate to kill the
possessed once they find them.

That's right. Lady Delta will carry out most of the
extermination, while Lady Epsilon will intercept the
Templars.

I'll be your backup. Prioritize the protection of the
possessed. Got it?
...Understood.
*fidget...fidget*
Grrr... I can't wait anymore!

Go ahead, Delta! Kick things off! I'll leave things
here to you!
Yaaaay! Let's doooo this!
Huh?!
You're my prey!
Gyaaaahhh!!!
Wha, wh-what?! Huh...?!
Next is youuu!
A-Ah! N-Noooo!
